Pre-Game Insights: Phoenix visits Philadelphia looking to stop its three-game road slide.
The 76ers have gone 5-9 at home. Philadelphia is 4-12 against opponents over .500.
The Suns are 5-10 on the road. Phoenix has a 4-8 record in games decided by at least 10 points.
The 76ers score 107.6 points per game, 6.8 fewer points than the 114.4 the Suns allow. The Suns average 112.1 points per game, 1.3 more than the 110.8 the 76ers allow.
Tyrese Maxey is averaging 25.2 points, 5.5 assists and 2.1 steals for the 76ers.
Devin Booker is averaging 24.6 points and 6.6 assists for the Suns.

In their last 10 games, the 76ers are 7-3, averaging 113.1 points, 38.9 rebounds, 22.8 assists, 11.5 steals and 4.4 blocks per game while shooting 46.9% from the field. Their opponents have averaged 111.2 points per game.

In their last 10 games, the Suns are 3-7, averaging 110.0 points, 41.0 rebounds, 27.3 assists, 8.0 steals and 5.9 blocks per game while shooting 46.8% from the field. Their opponents have averaged 115.5 points.
Others: 76ers injuries: Jared McCain (out, meniscus), Kelly Oubre Jr. (day to day, hand), KJ Martin (out, foot).
Suns injuries: Royce O'Neale (out, ankle), Tyus Jones (day to day, illness), Oso Ighodaro (day to day, illness).
